      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Unfortunately, it's not as easy as that :)\nI hope to find the time to identify the biggest bottlenecks and see if they can be fixed. But that won't happen before the tapeout, at least.\n\nThe IHP KLayout DRC is only that fast because they split the rule deck and run N instances in parallel. You could do the same here (and I'll look into it), but the gf180mcu KLayout DRC implementation is much more memory hungry, so with e.g. 64 GB, I can't run many threads in parallel at all.",
